expedDevRole.name: expedDevRole
expedDevRole.description: Defines the current role of this device. cpe (1) is a Customer Premises Equipment, bssActive(2) is a Base Station System which is controlling the system of CPE devices, and bssBackup(3) is a Base Station system which is currently connected, but not controlling the system (not currently used). In general, if this device is a 'cpe', its role will not change during operation or between reboots. If the device is a 'bss' it may change between bssActive and bssBackup and back again during normal operation. At this time, the NextNet Expedience system does not support the concept of a backup BSS, bssBackup is included for completeness.

expedDevDateTime.name: expedDevDateTime
expedDevDateTime.description: The date and time, with optional timezone information.

expedDevSerialNumber.name: expedDevSerialNumber
expedDevSerialNumber.description: The manufacturer's serial number for this device.

expedDevSTPControl.name: expedDevSTPControl
expedDevSTPControl.description: This object controls operation of the spanning tree protocol (as distinguished from transparent bridging). If set to stEnabled(1) then the spanning tree protocol is enabled, subject to bridging constraints. If noStFilterBpdu(2), then spanning tree is not active, and Bridge PDUs received are discarded. If noStPassBpdu(3) then spanning tree is not active and Bridge PDUs are transparently forwarded. Note that a device need not implement all of these options, but that noStFilterBpdu(2) is required.

expedDevGpsStatus.name: expedDevGpsStatus
expedDevGpsStatus.description: The status string coming from the GPS

expedDevGpsMonitorState.name: expedDevGpsMonitorState
expedDevGpsMonitorState.description: The state of the GPS Clock Monitor. The following states are possible. gCState-NoGps (No GPS for this base station), gCState-Init (Waiting for init to complete), gCState-Correcting (initial time solved, needs correction) gCState-Undetermined (floating init time solution), gCState-Unreliable (init time drifted too far), gCState-Locked (full time solution), gCState-Floating (Floating full time solution), and gCState-Drifted (full time solution drifted too far.

expedDevGpsClockOK.name: expedDevGpsClockOK
expedDevGpsClockOK.description: Indicates whether the GPS timing pulse is considered valid. If a base is operating without a GPS unit, then this element will be True.

expedDevPpsStatus.name: expedDevPpsStatus
expedDevPpsStatus.description: Indicates whether the one-second timing pulse is being delivered to the base station. If a base is operating with a GPS unit, then the timing pulse refers to the pulse being delivered by the GPS unit.

expedDevWriteFlash.name: expedDevWriteFlash
expedDevWriteFlash.description: Setting this flag to enable will cause the configuration to be written to flash

expedDevRebootDevice.name: expedDevRebootDevice
expedDevRebootDevice.description: Setting this flag to enable will cause the device to be rebooted

expedDevModelId.name: expedDevModelId
expedDevModelId.description: Model Identifier for the base station. The primary hardware features of the base station are specified by this string representation of a hexidecimal, 32-bit number with a range of 00000000 - FFFFFFFF and a format of ABCCDDEE. A => Model Category 0 => Outdoor Base Station 1 => Indoor CPE 2 => Outdoor CPE 3 => Indoor Base Station 4 => Mobile Subscriber Unit B => Reserved 0 => Default CC => Board Type 01 => FPGA Wedge 02 => Dual Board ASIC Wedge, Davicom 03 => Single Board ASIC Wedge, SMSC, Indoor 04 => Single Board ASIC, SMSC, Outdoor 05 => Slimline, ASIC 12 => AMOD Dual Board, ASIC 15 => AMOD Slimline, ASIC 16 => AMOD 5407 Coldfire, ASIC 17 => AMOD LX CPE 18 => AMOD LX SoC CPE 22 => AMOD 5484 Coldfire, ASIC Base DD => Reserved 00 => 2.6 GHz 01 => 3.3 GHz 02 => 3.5 GHz 03 => 2.4 GHz 04 => 2.3 GHz 05 => 700MHz 06 => 3.7 GHz EE => Special Options 00 => External Antenna 01 => Vertical Antenna 02 => Horizontal Antenna

expedDevSwCurrentVers.name: expedDevSwCurrentVers
expedDevSwCurrentVers.description: The software version currently operating in this device.

expedDevBootState.name: expedDevBootState
expedDevBootState.description: If operational(1), the device has completed loading and processing of configuration parameters and the Base Station is operational. If airlinkdisabled(2) then the device was administratively disabled. If privatemode(3), the device is operational and is in privatemode.

expedDevDhcp.name: expedDevDhcp
expedDevDhcp.description: The IP address of the DHCP server that assigned an IP address to this device. Returns 0.0.0.0 if DHCP was not used for IP address assignment.

expedDevFTPPort.name: expedDevFTPPort
expedDevFTPPort.description: The port number that FTP is listening on.

expedDevFTPRemote.name: expedDevFTPRemote
expedDevFTPRemote.description: The IP address mask that is allowed access to FTP. 255.255.255.255 allows access to everyone.

expedDevFTPTimeout.name: expedDevFTPTimeout
expedDevFTPTimeout.description: The max timeout in seconds to allow an FTP session to remain idle.

expedDevHostTraceAddress.name: expedDevHostTraceAddress
expedDevHostTraceAddress.description: The MAC address of the host to trace for debugging host traffic.

expedDevHostTraceFilter.name: expedDevHostTraceFilter
expedDevHostTraceFilter.description: This parameter allows a user to filter out host trace messages (i.e. discard them) for broadcast, or uplink or downlink frames.

expedDevTelnetPort.name: expedDevTelnetPort
expedDevTelnetPort.description: The port number that Telnet is listening on.

expedDevTelnetRemote.name: expedDevTelnetRemote
expedDevTelnetRemote.description: The IP address mask that is allowed access to Telnet. 255.255.255.255 allows access to everyone.

expedDevTelnetTimeout.name: expedDevTelnetTimeout
expedDevTelnetTimeout.description: The max timeout in seconds to allow a Telnet session to remain idle.

expedDevWebPort.name: expedDevWebPort
expedDevWebPort.description: The port number that WEB is listening on. This object is obsolete as of base station software version 4.3 and has no replacement.

expedDevWebRemote.name: expedDevWebRemote
expedDevWebRemote.description: The IP address mask that is allowed access to Web. 255.255.255.255 allows access to everyone. This object is obsolete as of base station software version 4.3 and has no replacement.

expedDevWebState.name: expedDevWebState
expedDevWebState.description: Enables/Disables WEB. This object is obsolete as of base station software version 4.3 and has no replacement.

expedDevVTTimeout.name: expedDevVTTimeout
expedDevVTTimeout.description: The max timeout in seconds to allow a Virtual Telnet session to wait for a reponse. This object is obsolete as of base station software version 4.3 and has no replacement.

expedDevVlanPortID.name: expedDevVlanPortID
expedDevVlanPortID.description: The Ethernet Port VLAN ID. The PVID is the VLAN ID that is applied to any received frames on the Ethernet port that are not tagged with a VLAN ID. This parameter only takes effect following a reboot of the base station. Setting to 0 disables this feature.

expedDevVlanLegacyID.name: expedDevVlanLegacyID
expedDevVlanLegacyID.description: The VLAN legacy ID. Selects the VLAN ID for all legacy CPEs that register with the base station. This parameter only takes effect following a reboot of the base station. A legacy CPE is defined as a CPE running 1.X code. Note that this VLAN ID is applied to all CPE's when AAA Authority is local. This object is obsolete as of base station software version 4.3 and is replaced by expedIfBssAAALocalVlan.

expedDevVlanMgmtID.name: expedDevVlanMgmtID
expedDevVlanMgmtID.description: The VLAN Management ID. Selects the VLAN ID of the management VLAN, which is the VLAN used by the local IP stack of the base stations. This parameter only takes effect following a reboot of the base station.

expedDevVlanUntaggedID.name: expedDevVlanUntaggedID
expedDevVlanUntaggedID.description: The VLAN Untagged ID. Configures the selected VLAN to transmit untagged frames (no 802.1Q tag). This parameter only takes effect following a reboot of the base station. Any Ethernet frames transmitted from the base station on this VLAN will be untagged. Setting to 0 disables this feature.

expedDevCpuUtilization.name: expedDevCpuUtilization
expedDevCpuUtilization.description: The current base station CPU utilization, expressed as a percentage.

expedDevEvSyslog.name: expedDevEvSyslog
expedDevEvSyslog.description: The IP address of the Syslog server. If 0.0.0.0, syslog transmission is inhibited.

expedDevEvControlTable.name: expedDevEvControlTable
expedDevEvControlTable.description: This table allows control of the reporting of event classes. For each event facility, the minimum level to send a syslog message and the minimum level to send a trap can be configured.

expedDevEvControlEntry.name: expedDevEvControlEntry
expedDevEvControlEntry.description: Allows configuration of the reporting mechanisms for a particular event priority.

expedDevEvFacility.name: expedDevEvFacility
expedDevEvFacility.description: The Facility Level to control for sending traps and syslog messages. log-fac-cfginit is used to control traps and syslog messagesfor configuration and initialization, log-fac-airlink-mac is used to control traps and syslog messagesfor the airlink mac, log-fac-nnmgr is used to control traps and syslog messages for the the airlink manager, log-fac-relay is used to control traps and syslog messages for the the relay, log-fac-stack is used to control traps and syslog messages for the the ip stack, log-fac-aaa is used to control traps and syslog messages for the aaa server, log-fac-ether-mac is used to control traps and syslog messages for the ethernet driver

expedDevEvSyslogMin.name: expedDevEvSyslogMin
expedDevEvSyslogMin.description: Defines the minimum level for sending a syslog message, all syslog messages at and above this level will be sent to the syslog server

expedDevEvTrapMin.name: expedDevEvTrapMin
expedDevEvTrapMin.description: Defines the minimum level for sending a syslog message, all syslog messages at and above this level will be sent to the SNMP manger as a trap

expedIfChannelId.name: expedIfChannelId
expedIfChannelId.description: The Base Station System identification of the channel within this particular MAC interface. If the interface is down, the object returns the most current value. If the channel ID is unknown, this object returns a value of 0. This object is obsolete as of base station software version 4.3 and is replaced by expedIfRadioFrequency.

expedIfChannelFrequency.name: expedIfChannelFrequency
expedIfChannelFrequency.description: The center of the frequency associated with the channel in use, which is stored in expedIfChannelId. The unit of this object is KHz. This object is obsolete as of base station software version 4.3 and is replaced by expedIfRadioFrequency.

expedIfChannelWidth.name: expedIfChannelWidth
expedIfChannelWidth.description: The width of the channel in use, which is stored in expedIfChannelId. Most implementations are expected to support a channel width of 6 MHz (North America) and/or 8 MHz (Europe). The unit of this object is KHz. This object is obsolete as of base station software version 4.3 and is replaced by expedIfRadioFrequency.

expedIfTXAGC.name: expedIfTXAGC
expedIfTXAGC.description: This specifies the automatic gain control (AGC) applied to the transmitter, for setting the maximum power output of the transmitter. This object is obsolete as of base station software version 4.3 and has no replacement.

expedIfAirlinkState.name: expedIfAirlinkState
expedIfAirlinkState.description: This enables and disables the airlink

expedIfRXAGC.name: expedIfRXAGC
expedIfRXAGC.description: This specifies the the automatic gain control applied to the receiver. This object is obsolete as of base station software version 4.3 and has no replacement.

expedIfAirlinkTiming.name: expedIfAirlinkTiming
expedIfAirlinkTiming.description: This selects the source for the one pulse-per-second. The source will either be external, meaning a GPS source, internal, or external pulse-per-second generated without a GPS unit. The time synchronization signal is needed to ascertain the proper timing for TDD (Time Division Duplexing).

expedIfAirlinkColorCode.name: expedIfAirlinkColorCode
expedIfAirlinkColorCode.description: This sets the home color code for this base station. The color code is broadcasted to all CPE's.

expedIfAirlinkExtRange.name: expedIfAirlinkExtRange
expedIfAirlinkExtRange.description: This sets the maximum cell size that is broadcasted to all CPE's. Each step indicates a 5 mile radius cell size. CPE's outside the advertised cell size will not try to register with this base.

expedIfBaseRegNotPref.name: expedIfBaseRegNotPref
expedIfBaseRegNotPref.description: Controls registration for this base. If set to True then this Base is advertising to other CPE's that it is busy and should try other bases first. This object is obsolete as of base station software version 4.3 and has no replacement.

expedIfBssDownChannelPower.name: expedIfBssDownChannelPower
expedIfBssDownChannelPower.description: The Base Station System operational transmit power. The range is 6 to 31 for 2 watts base, 10 to 31 for 2 watts base and 16 to 31 for 0.5 watts base. If the interface is down, this object either returns the configured value, the most current value or the value of 0.

expedIfBssDownChannelPowerLimit.name: expedIfBssDownChannelPowerLimit
expedIfBssDownChannelPowerLimit.description: The minimum limit of the Base Station System operational transmit power. The value is 16 for 0.5 watts base, 10 for 2 watts base, and 6 for 5 watts base.

expedIfBssDownlinkBias.name: expedIfBssDownlinkBias
expedIfBssDownlinkBias.description: The Base Station System Downlink Bias. This Bias sets up the number of uplink and downlink slots.

expedIfBssDownSlots.name: expedIfBssDownSlots
expedIfBssDownSlots.description: Directs the Base Station to transmit this number of down link symbols in each frame. Note that this number must be related to the number of up link symbols as follows: (Down Link Symbols) = (Up Link Symbols) + (Down Link Up Link Bias) * 4.

expedIfBssUpSlots.name: expedIfBssUpSlots
expedIfBssUpSlots.description: Directs the Base Station to expect this number of up link symbols in each frame. This is the number of down link symbols that will contain an UCS field. A CPE determines the existence of an up link symbol slot by detecting this UCS. This is a system wide configuration number and is used by the CPEs to facilitate frame synchronization. This number is to be a multiple of three (0,3,6,x). If this number is 0 then the system will be set up for continuous down link operation, allowing no up link operation.

expedIfAirlinkPowerControl.name: expedIfAirlinkPowerControl
expedIfAirlinkPowerControl.description: Enables and disables the airlink power control task. This task when enabled will shut the airlink down when power goes below a pre-determined power level or goes above a pre-determined power level.

expedIfUplinkSlotUsageTable.name: expedIfUplinkSlotUsageTable
expedIfUplinkSlotUsageTable.description: At the CPE, describes the PHY signal quality of downstream channels. At the BSS, describes the PHY signal quality of upstream channels.

expedIfUplinkSlotUsageEntry.name: expedIfUplinkSlotUsageEntry
expedIfUplinkSlotUsageEntry.description: Status information for an uplink slot.

expedIfUplinkSlotUsageIndex.name: expedIfUplinkSlotUsageIndex
expedIfUplinkSlotUsageIndex.description: Index value to uniquely identify an entry in this table, on a per-slot basis.

expedIfUplinkSlotUsageUseCount.name: expedIfUplinkSlotUsageUseCount
expedIfUplinkSlotUsageUseCount.description: Number of good symbols in slot.

expedIfUplinkSlotUsageRetryCount.name: expedIfUplinkSlotUsageRetryCount
expedIfUplinkSlotUsageRetryCount.description: Number of symbols that had to be retried.

expedIfUplinkSlotUsageBytesRecvd.name: expedIfUplinkSlotUsageBytesRecvd
expedIfUplinkSlotUsageBytesRecvd.description: Number of bytes in the received messages.

expedIfUplinkSlotTotUseCount.name: expedIfUplinkSlotTotUseCount
expedIfUplinkSlotTotUseCount.description: Number of good symbols in all 6 slots combined.

expedIfUplinkSlotTotFreeCount.name: expedIfUplinkSlotTotFreeCount
expedIfUplinkSlotTotFreeCount.description: Number of free slots in all 6 slots combined.

expedIfUplinkSlotTotRetryCount.name: expedIfUplinkSlotTotRetryCount
expedIfUplinkSlotTotRetryCount.description: Number of symbols that had to be retried in all 6 slots combined.

expedIfUplinkSlotTotBytesRecvd.name: expedIfUplinkSlotTotBytesRecvd
expedIfUplinkSlotTotBytesRecvd.description: Number of bytes in the received messages in all 6 slots combined.

expedIfUplinkSlotTotMsgsRecvd.name: expedIfUplinkSlotTotMsgsRecvd
expedIfUplinkSlotTotMsgsRecvd.description: Number of received messages in all 6 slots combined.

expedIfDownlinkBytes.name: expedIfDownlinkBytes
expedIfDownlinkBytes.description: Number of bytes on the downlink.

expedIfDownlinkSymbolsUsed.name: expedIfDownlinkSymbolsUsed
expedIfDownlinkSymbolsUsed.description: Number of symbols used on the downlink.

expedIfDownlinkSymbolsFree.name: expedIfDownlinkSymbolsFree
expedIfDownlinkSymbolsFree.description: Number of symbols free on the downlink.

expedIfDownlinkMsgsUnicast.name: expedIfDownlinkMsgsUnicast
expedIfDownlinkMsgsUnicast.description: Number of messages on the downlink that are unicast.

expedIfDownlinkMsgsNUnicast.name: expedIfDownlinkMsgsNUnicast
expedIfDownlinkMsgsNUnicast.description: Number of messages on the downlink that are broadcast.

expedIfDownlinkSaturation.name: expedIfDownlinkSaturation
expedIfDownlinkSaturation.description: Percent of slot usage on the downlink.

expedIfUplinkSaturation.name: expedIfUplinkSaturation
expedIfUplinkSaturation.description: Percent of saturation on the uplink.

expedIfMaxModLevel.name: expedIfMaxModLevel
expedIfMaxModLevel.description: Maximum modulation level for base. The acceptable values are 0 (QPSK), 1 (16 QAM), 2 (64 QAM) and 5 (16 QAM Lite).

expedIfMaxModLevelString.name: expedIfMaxModLevelString
expedIfMaxModLevelString.description: Maximum modulation level for base in string format.

expedIfMaxModLevelLimit.name: expedIfMaxModLevelLimit
expedIfMaxModLevelLimit.description: The limit of the maximum modulation level for base. The acceptable values are 0 (QPSK), 1 (16 QAM), 2 (64 QAM) and 5 (16 QAM Lite).

expedIfSoftRssi.name: expedIfSoftRssi
expedIfSoftRssi.description: This setting represents a transmit limit on the registered CPEs. A CPE will reduce its transmit power if its downlink RSSI is greater than this value. Transmit power will be reduced by the difference between the downlink RSSI and this value.

expedIfRadioFrequency.name: expedIfRadioFrequency
expedIfRadioFrequency.description: This object represents the configured frequency and bandwidth for the Airlink tranceiver in the target base station device. The format of this string is <frequency>-<bandwidth>[:<alias>]. The frequency specifies the center frequency in KHz. This value must be a multiple of 250, have exactly 7 decimal digits, and fall between the low and high frequency calibration points for the target base station device. The bandwidth specifies the width of the frequency in HKz. This value must be one of the following: 2500, 2750, 3000, 3500, 4000, 5000, 5500, 6000, 7000, or 8000. Most implementations are expected to support a channel width of 6000 KHz (North America) and/or 8000 KHz (Europe). This object replaces the expedIfChannelId, expedIfChannelFrequency, and expedIfChannelWidth objects.

expedIfMaxNumOfCPEs.name: expedIfMaxNumOfCPEs
expedIfMaxNumOfCPEs.description: Maximum cpes supported by the base DB.

expedIfMaxNumOfCPEsLimit.name: expedIfMaxNumOfCPEsLimit
expedIfMaxNumOfCPEsLimit.description: The limit of the maximum cpes supported by the base DB.

expedIfMaxNumOfHosts.name: expedIfMaxNumOfHosts
expedIfMaxNumOfHosts.description: Maximum hosts supported by the base DB.

expedIfBssCapabilities.name: expedIfBssCapabilities
expedIfBssCapabilities.description: Identifies the capabilities of the BSS MAC implementation at this interface. Note that packet transmission is always supported. Therefore, there is no specific bit required to explicitely indicate this capability.

expedIfBssNumOfCPEs.name: expedIfBssNumOfCPEs
expedIfBssNumOfCPEs.description: Number of CPE's currently registered on the Base station

expedIfBssNumOfHosts.name: expedIfBssNumOfHosts
expedIfBssNumOfHosts.description: Number of Hosts currently registered on the Base station

expedIfBssNumOfCPEsHighMark.name: expedIfBssNumOfCPEsHighMark
expedIfBssNumOfCPEsHighMark.description: Highest Number of CPE's that were registered on the Base station

expedIfBssNumOfHostsHighMark.name: expedIfBssNumOfHostsHighMark
expedIfBssNumOfHostsHighMark.description: Highest Number of Hosts that were registered on the Base station

expedIfBssRelayCpeIdleTime.name: expedIfBssRelayCpeIdleTime
expedIfBssRelayCpeIdleTime.description: The amount of time in seconds that the CPE can be idle before it is deleted from the base station. Idle time is defined as no uplink traffic from the CPE.

expedIfBssRelayDHCPAgentCircuitId.name: expedIfBssRelayDHCPAgentCircuitId
expedIfBssRelayDHCPAgentCircuitId.description: Indicate whether a relay DHCP agent circuit id is attached to all the client-to-server DHCP messages.

expedIfBssRelayDHCPAgentRemoteId.name: expedIfBssRelayDHCPAgentRemoteId
expedIfBssRelayDHCPAgentRemoteId.description: Indicate whether a relay DHCP agent remote id is attached to all the client-to-server DHCP messages.

expedIfBssRelayDHCPNumAddAgentFail.name: expedIfBssRelayDHCPNumAddAgentFail
expedIfBssRelayDHCPNumAddAgentFail.description: The number of failing to add agent circuit id and/or remote id in the client-to-server DHCP packets due to not enough space in the packets.

expedIfBssRelayDHCPNumDiscardExtraRelayI.name: expedIfBssRelayDHCPNumDiscardExtraRelayInfo
expedIfBssRelayDHCPNumDiscardExtraRelayI.description: The number of DHCP packets discarded due to the existing relay agent information in the client-to-server DHCP packet when adding DHCP agent circuit id and/or remote id to it.

expedIfBssRelayDHCPNumDiscardNoEnd.name: expedIfBssRelayDHCPNumDiscardNoEnd
expedIfBssRelayDHCPNumDiscardNoEnd.description: The number of DHCP packets discarded due to DHCP_END option missing when adding DHCP agent circuit id and/or remote id to client-to-server DHCP packets.

expedIfBssRelayDHCPTimeout.name: expedIfBssRelayDHCPTimeout
expedIfBssRelayDHCPTimeout.description: The amount of time in seconds waiting for completion of the DHCP conversation.

expedIfBssRelayMaxSSTransit.name: expedIfBssRelayMaxSSTransit
expedIfBssRelayMaxSSTransit.description: The max amount of time in 10ths of a second a sync session frame can live within the device before it is considered stale and is deleted.

expedIfBssRelayMaxTransit.name: expedIfBssRelayMaxTransit
expedIfBssRelayMaxTransit.description: The max amount of time in 10ths of a second a datagram frame can live within the device before it is considered stale and is deleted.

expedIfBssRelayIPHosts.name: expedIfBssRelayIPHosts
expedIfBssRelayIPHosts.description: The current number of dynamic hosts that have IP access using DHCP.

expedIfBssRelayPPPOEHosts.name: expedIfBssRelayPPPOEHosts
expedIfBssRelayPPPOEHosts.description: The current number of dynamic hosts that have PPPoE access. This count does not include PPPoE access by static IP hosts.

expedIfBssAAAConnectionTime.name: expedIfBssAAAConnectionTime
expedIfBssAAAConnectionTime.description: Date and Time of the current AAA connection.

expedIfBssAAAConnectionAttempts.name: expedIfBssAAAConnectionAttempts
expedIfBssAAAConnectionAttempts.description: Number of attempts for the current AAA connection.

expedIfBssAAAConfigConnection.name: expedIfBssAAAConfigConnection
expedIfBssAAAConfigConnection.description: The configuration parameter that controls the address of the AAA server(s). This can be one or two IP addresses, separated by a space or comma, to specify a primary and a backup AAA server. expedIfBssAAACurrentConnection shows the IP address currently being used.

expedIfBssAAACurrentConnection.name: expedIfBssAAACurrentConnection
expedIfBssAAACurrentConnection.description: IP address of the current AAA connection.

expedIfBssAAAAuthority.name: expedIfBssAAAAuthority
expedIfBssAAAAuthority.description: The Authority can be either local or remote. Local uses local authority parameters defined in ExpedIfBssLocalConfig for CPE permissions. Remote looks for authority from a Remote AAA Server for CPE permissions.

expedIfBssAAACaching.name: expedIfBssAAACaching
expedIfBssAAACaching.description: Enables/Disables aaa caching during remote authority. When enabled if the cpe is known by the base then the base will act as a cache and give authorization based on the last registration. This object is obsolete as of base station software version 4.3 and has no replacement.

expedIfBssAAAPort.name: expedIfBssAAAPort
expedIfBssAAAPort.description: The Port the AAA Server is listening on.

expedIfBssLocalAllow.name: expedIfBssLocalAllow
expedIfBssLocalAllow.description: The permission the Local Authority gives to each CPE, where enable allows CPEs to register, and disable disallows CPEs to register. Note: When a CPE is disallowed the CPE must be rebooted in order to register with this base station again. This defaults to enable

expedIfBssLocalHosts.name: expedIfBssLocalHosts
expedIfBssLocalHosts.description: The number of hosts Local Authority allows behind each CPE. This defaults to 10

expedIfBssLocalSla.name: expedIfBssLocalSla
expedIfBssLocalSla.description: The Service Level Agreement (SLA) parameters given to each CPE. This is of the form up-down, where up and down are decimal numbers between 0 and 10000, inclusive, separated by a dash character. This defaults to 100-100.

expedIfBssLocalVlan.name: expedIfBssLocalVlan
expedIfBssLocalVlan.description: The VLAN identifier Local Authority assigns to each CPE. This object replaces the expedDevVlanLegacyID object. This defaults to 1.

expedIfBssLocalVoipAddress.name: expedIfBssLocalVoipAddress
expedIfBssLocalVoipAddress.description: The VoIP server address Local Authority assigns to each CPE. allows the VoIP use through the CPE and disable disallows VoIP use through the CPE. This defaults to 0.0.0.0.

expedIfBssLocalVoipState.name: expedIfBssLocalVoipState
expedIfBssLocalVoipState.description: The VoIP state Local Authority assigns to each CPE, where enable allows the VoIP use through the CPE and disable disallows VoIP use through the CPE. This defaults to enable.

expedIfBssAAARegRequests.name: expedIfBssAAARegRequests
expedIfBssAAARegRequests.description: Number of CPE registration requests received over the air.

expedIfBssAAARegDenys.name: expedIfBssAAARegDenys
expedIfBssAAARegDenys.description: Number of permission vectors that indicate a deny for a CPE registration.

expedIfBssAAARegConfirms.name: expedIfBssAAARegConfirms
expedIfBssAAARegConfirms.description: Number of permission vectors that indicate a confirm for a CPE registration.

expedIfBssAAARegCache.name: expedIfBssAAARegCache
expedIfBssAAARegCache.description: Number of registration confirms due to caching. This object is obsolete as of base station software version 4.3 and has no replacement.

expedIfBssAAARegDuplicates.name: expedIfBssAAARegDuplicates
expedIfBssAAARegDuplicates.description: Number of registration requests that are duplicates of a current registration request. Indicates that a second registration was received for a given CPE before the permission vector was received from the AAA server.

expedIfBssAAANoAAAResponse.name: expedIfBssAAANoAAAResponse
expedIfBssAAANoAAAResponse.description: Number of registration requests that never received a permission vector from the AAA server.

expedIfBssAAACDRsSent.name: expedIfBssAAACDRsSent
expedIfBssAAACDRsSent.description: Number of CDR's sent to the AAA server.

expedIfBssAAAPVsRecv.name: expedIfBssAAAPVsRecv
expedIfBssAAAPVsRecv.description: Number of PV's received from the AAA server.

expedIfBssAAAUnexpectedPV.name: expedIfBssAAAUnexpectedPV
expedIfBssAAAUnexpectedPV.description: Number of PV's received from the AAA server, that were not expected.

expedIfBssAAADroppedCDRS.name: expedIfBssAAADroppedCDRS
expedIfBssAAADroppedCDRS.description: Number of CDR's dropped due to out of buffer condition.

expedIfBssAAADeregCPE.name: expedIfBssAAADeregCPE
expedIfBssAAADeregCPE.description: Total number of de-reg CPE PV's.

expedIfBssAAABindIP.description: Total number of bind IP PV's.
